Changing and Adding lifecycle policies 
1.Azure portal Code view 
In the azure portal navigate to the storage account
Under Data management select lifecycle management to view or change lifecycle management policies
Select the Code view tab on this sab you can define a lifecycle management policy in json
{
  "rules": [
    {
      "enabled": true,
      "name": "move-to-cool",
      "type": "Lifecycle",
      "definition": {
        "actions": {
          "baseBlob": {
            "tierToCool": {
              "daysAfterModificationGreaterThan": 30
            }
          }
        },
        "filters": {
          "blobTypes": [
            "blockBlob"
          ],
          "prefixMatch": [
            "sample-container/log"
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

Azure CLI
Create a Json file called policy.json and add it using Azure CLI
az storage account management-policy create 
--account-name <storage-account> 
--policy @policy.json 
--resource-group <resource-group>
